1978;;Slow Dancing in the Big City;;American;;John G. Avildsen;;Paul Sorvino, Anne Ditchburn;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slow_Dancing_in_the_Big_City;;Lou Friedlander (Paul Sorvino) is a popular columnist for the New York Daily News, writing about the little people of bustling New York City while befriending a street boy named Marty (Adam Gifford). His life changes dramatically upon falling in love with neighbor Sarah Gantz (Anne Ditchburn), a young ballerina who had just discovered she is stricken with a debilitating condition that will eventually force her to quit dancing.